x,y,z >0
 x+y+z=\dfrac{\pi}{2}
\sin{x}\sqrt{1-\sin{x}}+\sin{y}\sqrt{1-\sin{y}}+\sin{z}\sqrt{1-\sin{z}}  \ge 4\sqrt{2} \sin{x}\sin{y}\sin{z}(\sin{x}+\sin{y}+\sin{z})
\frac{1}{\sin}
\sin
\sqrt{1-\sin x} = \sqrt{2}\sin\left(\frac{\pi}{4}-\frac{x}{2}\right) = \sqrt{2}\sin\left(\frac{y+z}{2}\right) \geq \frac{1}{2}\sqrt{2}\left( \sin y + \sin z\right).
\sin x \sqrt{1-\sin x}+\sin y \sqrt{1-\sin y} + \sin z \sqrt{1-\sin z} \geq \sqrt{2}\left(\sin x \sin y+ \sin x \sin z + \sin y \sin z\right) \\ = \sqrt{2}\sin x \sin y \sin z\left(\frac{1}{\sin x} + \frac{1}{\sin y} + \frac{1}{\sin z} \right) \\ \geq \sqrt{2}\sin x \sin y \sin z \frac{3}{\sin\frac{\pi}{6}}=6 \sqrt{2}\sin x \sin y \sin z
\sin x + \sin y + \sin z \leq 3 \sin \frac{\pi}{6} = \frac{3}{2} 
